urls.description: Solid state is a very broad term for the reduction or elimination of all liquid or semi-liquid materials in a battery and results in a completely solid battery. Current batteries have liquid electrolytes that are usually some sort of gel. Solid state technology, such as the one developed by Elecjet, replaces the liquid electrolyte with a solid sheet-like material such as ceramic oxide.
